\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces  The two plots on the left show average reward per episode on Breakout and Seaquest respectively during training. The statistics were computed by running an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$ for 10000 steps. The two plots on the right show the average maximum predicted action-value of a held out set of states on Breakout and Seaquest respectively. One epoch corresponds to 50000 minibatch weight updates or roughly 30 minutes of training time.}}{7}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig-V}{{2}{7}{The two plots on the left show average reward per episode on Breakout and Seaquest respectively during training. The statistics were computed by running an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$ for 10000 steps. The two plots on the right show the average maximum predicted action-value of a held out set of states on Breakout and Seaquest respectively. One epoch corresponds to 50000 minibatch weight updates or roughly 30 minutes of training time}{figure.2}{}}
