\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces  The upper table compares average total reward for various learning methods by running an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$ for a fixed number of steps. The lower table reports results of the single best performing episode for HNeat and DQN. HNeat produces deterministic policies that always get the same score while DQN used an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$.}}{8}{table.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{table-results}{{1}{8}{The upper table compares average total reward for various learning methods by running an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$ for a fixed number of steps. The lower table reports results of the single best performing episode for HNeat and DQN. HNeat produces deterministic policies that always get the same score while DQN used an $\epsilon $-greedy policy with $\epsilon =0.05$}{table.1}{}}
